# Approved artifacts. One line per category. Paths are relative to prototype/.
# Edit when an artifact's approval state changes; the launcher and skills read
# this file to know which versions are the source of truth.
#
# Categories used by the toolchain:
#   prd:        the approved PRD (e.g., prd/site-prd.md)
#   cujs:       set to "aligned" once CUJs are signed off
#   styles:     the selected style preview (e.g., styles/cool-minimal.html)
#   wireframes: set to "aligned" once wireframes are signed off
#   prototype:  the selected interactive prototype (e.g., hi-fi/cool-minimal-v1.html)
#   theme:      the active theme tokens file (typically tokens.css)
#   components: set when extracted from the approved prototype
#   frames:     set to "aligned" once a frame template is picked for the project
#   target:     the rendering target / form factor for prototypes and wireframes.
#               Common values:
#                 web-spa            - default, no device frame
#                 phone-ios          - iPhone shape (Apple HIG)
#                 phone-android      - Pixel shape (Material 3)
#                 tablet-ipados      - iPad (Apple HIG)
#                 tablet-android     - Android large screen (Material 3)
#                 watch-watchos      - Apple Watch (Apple HIG)
#                 watch-wear-os      - Wear OS smartwatch
#                 tv-tvos            - Apple TV
#                 tv-android-tv      - Android TV / Google TV
#                 desktop-macos      - macOS app
#                 desktop-windows    - Windows app (Microsoft Fluent 2)
#                 xr-visionos        - Apple Vision Pro
#                 xr-horizon         - Meta Quest
#                 auto-carplay       - Apple CarPlay
#                 auto-android-auto  - Android Auto / Automotive OS
#                 terminal           - TUI / CLI
#               See styles/design-guidelines.html for the canonical vendor
#               reference each target maps to.
#
# Item-level matches render a "✓ Selected" pill on the matching card in the
# launcher list view (prototypes, styles). Section/list keys also render a
# small green check next to the section header / sidebar list label so the
# user can see at a glance which categories have been aligned.
#
# Skills write into this file when the user signs off:
#   prd-crit          → writes/updates `prd:` when PRD is marked Ready
#   map-cujs          → writes/updates `cujs:` when CUJs are aligned
#   design-themes     → writes/updates `styles:` and `theme:` when committed
#   design-wireframes → writes/updates `wireframes:` when aligned
#   design-prototypes → writes/updates `prototype:` when user picks "the one"
#                       reads `target:` to choose the right frame template
#   design-components → reads `prototype:`; writes `components:` after extraction
#   prototype-init    → writes initial `target:` based on user's project type
#
# Add categories ad-hoc as needed; tools that don't recognize a key just ignore it.

target: web-spa
